7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Codacy AI and Continue share a solid foundation of core features including Debugging, Multi Language. Where Codacy AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Review, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Continue uniquely offers Autocomplete and Code Generation and Refactoring and Ide Integration and Chat, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Codacy AI holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Continue scores 7/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Continue comes in at a lower starting price of $0, while Codacy AI begins at $15/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Codacy AI's free tier and Continue's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
