b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Codacy AI is best suited for teams enforcing code quality standards, CI/CD integration, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Continue, meanwhile, shines for developers wanting full control, teams using self hosted LLMs, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Codacy AI describes itself as \"Automated code quality with AI-powered analysis.\" Continue, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Open-source AI code assistant you can customize.\" With 11 years between them, Codacy AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Continue offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Continue** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (7 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Codacy AI is a poor choice — far from it. Codacy AI excels in its own right, particularly for teams enforcing code quality standards and CI/CD integration.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value fully open-source, go with Continue. If established code quality platform matters more to you, Codacy AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
